column12: Welcome to The RMHAM DMR Machine, located on Cheyenne Mountain above Colorado Springs This machine sits atop Cheyenne Mountain overlooking Colorado Springs and Pueblo. The talkgroups that are setup on this system are the Fun Machine Analog transcoded and statically linked on TS1 as TG310815. column12: The First Mac Pass Repeater Group DMR Repeater in New Mexico Sandia Crest 2 miles East of Albuquerque, NM. 10,600 Feet Elevation. 50 watt Hytera RD985 Repeater. Dual Mix with Analog, PL 131.8. Receive Antenna is Directional to the West at 10 db gain, the Transmit antenna is a Celwave PD-1151 8dBd omni pattern. Tower height is 65 feet, repeater antennas are on top. The repeater is working very, very well and no RF Noise issues on the mountain. On the air April 27, 2019.
Features: Brandmeister Networ on DMR Dual Mix Repeater with Analog on PL Tone 131.8
